==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Ripsaw
<hw>Rip"saw`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <ety>[See <er>Rip</er>, <pos>v.
t.</pos>, 4.]</ety> <fld>(Carp.)</fld> <def>A handsaw with coarse teeth
which have but a slight set, used for cutting wood in the direction of
the grain (the fiber); -- called also <altname>ripping
saw</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

